This paper deals with morphological analysis of languages, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a deep neural network-based model for morphological analysis, which involves multitask learning and joint prediction of multiple morphological tags. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). 

The paper also mentions the use of effective training strategies and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning (ML) research. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). 

Finally, the paper mentions the use of a genetic algorithm for optimizing character-level features, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY). 

Therefore, the 5 likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely, are: cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY.
